   1 import urllib.request
   2 import tensorflow as tf
   3 import itertools
   4 
   5 URL = 'http://download.tensorflow.org/data/fsns-20160927/testdata/fsns-00000-of-00001'
   6 DST_ORIG = 'fsns-00000-of-00001.orig'
   7 DST = 'fsns-00000-of-00001'
   8 KEEP_NUM_RECORDS = 5
   9 
  10 print('Downloading %s ...' % URL)
  11 urllib.request.urlretrieve(URL, DST_ORIG)
  12 
  13 print('Writing %d records from %s to %s ...' % (KEEP_NUM_RECORDS, DST_ORIG, DST))
  14 with tf.io.TFRecordWriter(DST) as writer:
  15     for raw_record in itertools.islice(tf.python_io.tf_record_iterator(DST_ORIG), KEEP_NUM_RECORDS):
  16         writer.write(raw_record)
